  "original_title": "1924  \u0db4\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0db4\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dda \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dd6 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dc3",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The change in the police after 1924",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Two female Deputy Inspector Generals of Police have been appointed as the Chairmanship of the Governing Committee of the Police Savings Association and as Committee Secretary.",
        "The 95th general meeting of the association was held today, where these appointments were made. This association was established in 1924 and since its inception, senior DIGs and DIGs have been appointed as the chairman of the governing committee.",
        "However, for the first time, Deputy Inspector General of Police Padmini Weerasuriya has been appointed as the Chairman of the Governing Committee of the Police Savings Association and Deputy Inspector General of Police Renuka Jayasundara has been appointed as the Committee Secretary.",
        "Mr. Police Inspector N. Priyadarshana is the administrative secretary of this association and he is the first police officer to hold the position of administrative secretary."
      ],
